        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-07T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="1640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8571/9–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-07T15:00:00+08:00">September 7, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 8—12:45 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3684. Tax bills mentioned mytel 3615, repeated Nanking 1895, Peiping 303,
                    September 2, have been returned rewritten.</p>
                <p>Taxpayer given as “former American Consulate” with extension deadline payment
                    date to September 20. Am acknowledging receipt repeating our regulations that in
                    accordance recognized principle of international comity, property one nation
                    within territory of another tax exempt when used for official purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
